# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CMS pipeline env — only needed on the host that runs content production.
#
# Init with:   cp .env.example.db .env.db
# OR:          ./scripts/ops/db/env.sh    # idempotent, injects smart defaults
#
# This file is consumed by:
#   - ./scripts/ops/db/content.sh  (sync / sentences / audio / publish / export)
#   - ./scripts/ops/db/bake_image.sh     (bake db image)
#
# It is NOT consumed by the backend container — the runtime is a pure read
# layer and never calls OpenAI / Tencent TTS. So you do NOT need this file
# on a target host that just `docker pull`s a content-baked db image.
#
# Three categories of variables:
#   1. External secrets (you MUST fill): AI_API_KEY, TENCENT_*
#   2. Bake-time identity (defaults provided, but must match the db image
#      labels you intend to bake with): POSTGRES_USER, POSTGRES_DB
#   3. Configuration (sensible defaults; override only if you know why):
#      AI_BASE_URL, AI_MODEL, AUDIO_DIR, DEFAULT_BUCKET_TARGET_SIZE,
#      DB_IMAGE_TAG, DOCKER_REGISTRY
#
# After editing, validate with:  ./scripts/ops/db/env.sh doctor
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# =========================================================================
# Database connection (REQUIRED for content.sh)
# Points at the dev/prod db from the host (localhost:5432, since compose
# exposes the port). Adjust if your DB lives elsewhere.
#
# env.sh does NOT auto-fill this — the password is host-side and you have
# to know it (or run ./scripts/prod/run.sh doctor to discover it).
# =========================================================================
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://english_user:change-me-postgres-password@localhost:5432/english_learning

# =========================================================================
# Bake-time identity (REQUIRED for bake_image.sh)
# These three are baked into the db image's labels. After the image is
# baked and pushed, target hosts discover them via `docker inspect` —
# no further configuration needed on the target.
#
# Change these ONLY if you really know what you're doing. Renaming the
# user/db after content has been baked invalidates the existing
# content_items table (different OWNER).
# =========================================================================
POSTGRES_USER=english_user
POSTGRES_DB=english_learning

# =========================================================================
# Image identity (REQUIRED for bake_image.sh + push_image.sh)
# - DB_IMAGE       Image name. Default: english_db_content
# - DB_IMAGE_TAG   Tag baked into the image + read back via image label
#                  (type-any-language.content.version). Use a version
#                  scheme (v0.0.1) not `latest`.
# - DOCKER_REGISTRY Registry namespace (e.g. docker.io/youruser).
#                    Leave empty to skip push (local-only mode).
# =========================================================================
DB_IMAGE=english_db_content
DB_IMAGE_TAG=v0.0.1
# DOCKER_REGISTRY=

# =========================================================================
# AI service (REQUIRED for `content.sh sentences`)
# OpenAI-compatible endpoint. Override AI_BASE_URL for Azure / proxies.
#
# env.sh will NOT auto-fill AI_API_KEY — that's a real secret you must
# obtain from the provider. https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# =========================================================================
AI_API_KEY=sk-your-real-api-key
AI_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1
AI_MODEL=gpt-3.5-turbo

# =========================================================================
# Audio / TTS (REQUIRED for `content.sh audio`)
# TENCENT_* are all-or-nothing: if any one is set, all three are required.
# Find credentials at: https://console.cloud.tencent.com/cam/capi
# =========================================================================
AUDIO_DIR=/backend/audio
TENCENT_SECRET_ID=
TENCENT_SECRET_KEY=
TENCENT_APP_ID=0

# =========================================================================
# Content pipeline tuning (OPTIONAL — has safe defaults)
# Default per-(lib, scenario) bucket size when generating sentences via
# `./scripts/ops/db/content.sh sentences` with no spec or override.
# =========================================================================
DEFAULT_BUCKET_TARGET_SIZE=200
